description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a Registered Nurse with a special interest in Neurology? If so, TeamNNUH’s Neuroscience team want to hear from you!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There has never been a better time to join the Neuroscience team at Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital as we have recently expanded with the introduction of a brand new ward and additional services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The MS nurse is part of a team of Neurology specialist nurses based in Neurology outpatients. You will provide direct patient care and support in helping improve quality of life by educating the patient on the management and control of symptoms and offering support following diagnosis. You will be the go-to resource for other health professionals and will work closely with the multi-disciplinary team. You will be working closely with all the Neurology consultants but still be making independent decisions around the care of the patient.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the team lead you will be expected to ensure the service meets the demands of our patients offering them a highly skilled service, whilst also supporting the other team members. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for someone to be part of a dynamic team who alongside their colleagues are in the process of becoming a Neuroscience Centre of Excellence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you have the experience, relevant qualifications and enthusiasm to excel within this role, please apply today!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note this is a full time role covering Monday to Friday.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time:&lt;/strong&gt; 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt; 25th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 4th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications:&lt;/strong&gt; 17th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marilyn Turner - Neurology Nurse Specialist&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01603 287267&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: marilyn.turner@nnuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
